Amadeus, IAG, Ezentis, Fersa Energias: Spanish Equity Preview

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-05-08T10:36:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-08/amadeus-iag-ezentis-fersa-energias-spanish-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Spanish trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are from the previous close.  Spain’s  IBEX 35 Index (IBEX)  dropped 0.2 percent to 10,610.5.  Spanish stocks:  Amadeus IT Holding SA (AMS)  : The Spanish flight-
reservations provider that sold shares to the public last April
is scheduled to report first-quarter earnings before the market
opens. The company will hold a webcast conference for investors
at 3 p.m. CET. The shares climbed 2.9 percent to 14.25 euros.  Fersa Energias Renovables SA (FRS)  : The  wind-energy 
developer aims to boost its installed capacity for wind energy
to 500 megawatts by 2013, Chairman Jose Maria Roger told
Expansion in an interview. The shares gained 1.6 percent to 1.29
euros.  Grupo Ezentis SA (EZE)  : The Spanish engineering company
plans to raise more than 40 million euros ($57 million) from the
sale of assets, Chairman Mario Armero told El Economista in an
interview. The shares slipped 0.5 percent to 41.3 euro cents.  International Consolidated Airlines Group SA (IAG SM): The
carrier formed from the combination of British Airways and
Iberia Lineas Aereas de Espana may make a bid for TAP SGPS SA,
 Portugal ’s state-owned airline, the Sunday Times said without
saying where it got the information. The shares jumped 3.7
percent to 2.87 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
 acullen8@bloomberg.net . 